# User Interview Notes — Session 1
**Date:** June 10, 2025
**Participant:** Sarah, Senior Designer, 2 years using the product
**Interviewer:** Ali

---

## Opening

**Q: Walk me through a typical day using the product.**

"I open it first thing in the morning and immediately get confused about where to pick up from yesterday. I have like six projects going at once and the homepage just shows everything in chronological order. It's overwhelming."

**Q: How long does it usually take you to find what you need?**

"Easily 3-4 minutes just to orient myself. I've started keeping a separate sticky note with what I was working on. That feels ridiculous."

---

## Pain Points

**Q: What frustrates you most about the product right now?**

"The navigation. I know the feature is there somewhere but I can't find it without clicking through three menus. I end up googling our own tool sometimes."

"Also search. If I search for something, I get too many results and I can't filter by project or date easily."

**Q: Has this ever caused you to not use the product?**

"Yes. Last week I just used email instead because setting up the workflow in the tool felt like too much work at that moment."

---

## Workarounds

**Q: How do you currently work around the navigation problem?**

"Bookmarks in my browser. I have like 15 bookmarked deep links. It's clunky but it works."

---

## Closing

**Q: If you could change one thing, what would it be?**

"A 'recently visited' section right on the homepage. Just show me the last 5 things I touched. That alone would save me so much time."
